  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "\n> that's not a correct solution, make the types pass properly, all other tests pass typescript @copilot \n\nFixed in commits 59a61e0 and 465f185. The issue was that tsconfig.json was missing the `lib` compiler option, which TypeScript needs to recognize standard JavaScript APIs like `Array.prototype.find()`. Added `\"lib\": [\"ES2020\", \"DOM\"]` to provide these type definitions. The test file now properly type-checks with Jest types being automatically loaded from `@types/jest` when node_modules is installed.",
    "created_at": "2026-01-14T10:06:45Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6865#issuecomment-3748760567",
    "id": 3748760567,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6865",
    "node_id": "IC_kwDOAlnbOs7fcYv3",
    "performed_via_github_app": {
